article.headline: Bradley 83, Missouri St. 71
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Daniel Ruffin had a game-high 25 points to lead Bradley to an 83-71 win over Missouri State on Wednesday night. Andrew Warren scored 19 points, Jeremy Crouch had 16 points and Theron Wilson added 13 points and 13 rebounds for Bradley (14-10, 7-5 Missouri Valley), which never trailed in the game and led 36-19 at the half. Bradley was 29-for-35, or 83 percent, from the free-throw line, compared with 14-for-19, or 74 percent, for Missouri State (11-13, 4-8). The Braves also had 12 3-pointers, while the Bears had seven. Missouri State outrebounded Bradley 38-35, but could not overcome the 20 points Bradley scored off turnovers. Deven Mitchell led Missouri State with 17 points. Dale Lamberth added 15 points and 10 rebounds and Justin Fuehrmeyer scored 14 points, including four 3-pointers, for the Bears.
